Comment: Jumped well, always in touch behind leader, swiftly moved to the lead near 250M, drew well clear and was never challenged to the line.
Shifted out abruptly on jumping, settled 2-wide in the group chasing the pace, angled out gradually to commence his run passing 450M, ran on strongly final 250M to go 2nd just before the line.
Hampered at the start, ended up behind midfield 5-6Ls from leader, held up early in straight, clear from 350M and ran on soundly to just miss out on 2nd.
Held an inside position behind leading group and had a smooth run throughout, kept on well early in straight and looked a place chance near 200M but run ended in late stages.
Driven early to find the lead, held advantage of just over 1L turning in found no response when the winner flashed past near 250M, faded gradually.
Ordinary jump but was taken to a 3-wide position in the chasing group, tucked in for cover making the turn, stayed on same pace and not able to land a serious blow.
Restrained to a midfield position along the fence, angled out for a clear run on straightening, had his chance but found no extra inside 150M.
Awkwardly away then raced towards the rear 6-7Ls off the pace, briefly held up early in straight but ran on only fairly when clear.
With leaders but was caught 4 wide on the outside, lacked pace to challenge turning into straight then weakened rapidly passing 200M.
6Ls behind leaders and never better than midfield, fanned wide into straight, driven inside 400M but no progress.
Settled 3-wide towards the back of the field, had plenty to do passing 400M but could keep on at the same pace only. Never a factor.
Trailed in last after a sluggish start, had 9Ls to make up turning in, not quickened and could get past badly tired runners only.
Settled towards the rear and not hurried in early stages, didn't pick up passing 450M, soon behind. (Bled.)
Up with the early pace but struggled to keep up passing 450M, weakened rapidly and finished tailed out. (Unacceptable performance.)
Made every post a winner. Opened up an advantage by the 200m, and was never headed.
One of the best away and from a wide gate was able to sit 1 off as joint leader by the 800m. Maintained a good gallop right to the wire.
Raced 3 back, 2-3 wide with some cover on the circle. Straightened up 5 wide and fought on gamely in the straight to snare a placing.

Blundered on jumping then recovered to enjoy a nice run in transit on the back of the leader along the paint. Raced in some restricted room early in the straight but found the place getters too strong.
Settled midfield the fence. Was niggled along after the 600m to improve, didn't get the best of runs in the home straight and was eased prior to the post.
Travelled midfield, 1 off with cover. Swung out into clear running rounding the home turn. Was somewhat one paced inside the last 200m.
Raced behind midfield, 3 deep with cover. Battled away gamely to the finish.
Positioned worse than midfield the fence. Made steady ground through the field over the concluding stages.
Settled with the backmakers, 3 wide with cover. Came widest in the straight and ran to the wire honestly.
Slow to begin settling in last position on the fence. Passed a few tiring horses in the run to the line.
Failed to muster speed early and settled well back in the event 2-3 wide with cover. Was unable to quicken in the run home.
Camped 1 out 1back. Had every chance, although was inclined to hang in over the last 400m.
Eventually gained cover near the 800m, to travel 3 wide in a midfield position. Was well and truly beaten by the final furlong.
Jumped awkwardly taking up a position close to midfield, 2 deep with cover. Was well beaten in the run to the wire.

Quickly into stride but not sufficient speed to lead. Under pressure until settling 2-wide behind leader near the bend. Rallied on to chase the leader and hit front 200M. Hung on to repel late challenge.
Away in line. Dropped towards rear in a 2-wide position from 1000M. 6Ls down on straightening. Finished off well but was held by the winner closing stages.
Raced within 4Ls of the pace on fence through to the home straight. Kept making up ground but not able to match on terms with the front pair. Clung on for 3rd.

Pressed early but failed to work across. Trapped 4-wide and was 3Ls behind the speed making the home turn. Kept giving but no hope with the front pair. Just denied a place at the post. (Tactic questioned.)

Jumped fairly well from high draw but no early speed. Gradually dropped towards rear in a 3-wide position before making home turn. Made steady headway in the straight but was beaten far by the principals. (Questioned.)

Shifted in at start and was soon shaken up to race 3-wide ahead of midfield from 1000M. Dropped to midfield passing 700M and was 4Ls away entering home straight. Picked up fairly and was steadied at 150M.
Fair start and was urged to go forward. Took lead on fence from 1100M and held a 1L advantage turning in. Fought on with the winner until headed 200M. Not much to offer thereafter.
Moderate start and was eased to rear from high draw. Travelled very wide throughout. Covered some ground in the straight.
Never far off the pace in a 2-wide position but failed to turn up a notch in the home straight.
Bumped at start and was taken towards rear on fence from 1200M. Took inside run and was 6Ls off rounding the turn. Slightly held up near 400M. Ran on fairly well before steadied at 100M.
2-wide behind midfield through to the home straight. Momentarily held up top of home straight but responded only fairly once into clear.
Hard ridden from high draw and travelled 3-wide in the leading section from 1000M. Couldn't quite follow and was beaten early in the straight.
Prominent early. Ridden vigorously from 600M but found nothing. Struggled home.
4-wide towards rear until eased down 250M from home. Finished tailed out.
Settled 3Ls behind leaders, shifted wider for home, responded well when asked for efforts from 400m, fought hard and took the lead passing 50m.
Jumped well from the inside draw and held a fence position just behind leaders, clicked into gear 350m, laid out badly passing 100m and grabbed by winner passing 50m.
Went forward to share the lead comfortably, was challenged 350m, kept battling but lacked extra pace to hold off leaders passing 100m.
Jumped well and tacked leaders prominently, responded well under pressure and progressed steadily down the outside, checked badly passing 100m.
Slow to begin, well back on fence 8Ls away, made considerable ground when asked for effort from 400m but offered little threat to the placegetters.
Towards the rear and not hurried in early and middle stages, moved closer 3-wide rounding bend, ran on steadily from 400m.
Awkwardly start, taken back 8Ls off the leader, made gradual ground to 100m before run ended.
Taken back on jumping from the outside draw, settled 7-8Ls behind leaders, made substantial ground when asked passing 400m, steadied 100m when the horse ahead was checked.
Out in line, sat within striking distance from the leader, eased to a fence position rounding bend at 800m, gave very limited response when asked for efforts early in straight, got tired 200m.
Settled 2-wide 5Ls back in midfield, struggled passing 600m, failed to make ground when asked for efforts from 400m.
Jumped fairly, went forward to share the lead, hung out early in straight and weakened passing 250m.
Began well, held up to obtain a fence position in midfield, slightly outpaced making the turn for home, failed to make up ground in straight.
Urged to place handy but caught 3-wide, drifted back rounding bend, could not keep up passing 600m and got tired early in straight.
Pushed forward to tack the lead but caught very wide with no cover, weakened sharply passing 300m and finished tailed out.
Reasonable break and soon occupied a prominent position in midfield. Picked up nicely early in the straight, finished off strongly and took the lead 150m out.
Jumped best, urged to be one out one back from leader, enjoyed a good run throughout, quickened well from 400m, briefly led near 200m but was soon caught by the winner.
Broke well, settled 2Ls off pace on rails, held up early in the straight, closed off well when clear passing 250m.
Broke well and fast into stride, took rails and led by 0.5L, headed by winner near 200m, kept on until flattening 100m.
Jumped fast but taken towards the rear division, 6Ls off pace 2-wide, proved difficult to settle in early stages, made up ground steadily down centre of the home straight from 200m.
Awkward start, fast into stride and sat one back on rails, started struggling rounding bend near 600m, hung on fairly well under hard riding in the home straight.
Awkwardly started, urged early to take a midfield position 3-wide with cover, was bumped and carried wider at the final turn, had chance in straight but just struck on at one speed.
Jumped fast, handily sat 2Ls off the pace 2-wide with cover, had every chance in the straight but never really troubled the principals.
Slow to begin but soon caught up 5Ls behind the leader, overraced badly until the 800m, swung widest for home, gave very limited response when asked for efforts final 400m.
Settled 2Ls off pace 3-wide without cover, travelled well until flattened near 300m.
No early speed, allowed to ease 8Ls off the pace, shifted widest but passed only tired runners in the home straight.
Bit slow to begin, urged to catch up 5Ls off the pace on rails, shifted wider for home, lacked a turn of foot and retreated at the 100m. (Mucus and blood in trachea, lame and wounded right hind.)
Reasonable break from the low draw, settled rearward 7Ls off the leader, blundered at 1200m, saved some ground rounding bend, made little ground to 250m before run ended.
Jumped fast but taken down to rails, 8-9Ls off speed throughout, failed to quicken when asked for efforts.
Eased to sit in midfield, 4.5Ls off the leaders 3 wide, favoured by the fast tempo, made ground steadily 350M to win by a very narrow margin.
Eased to sit in midfield, 4.5Ls off the leaders 2 wide, benefited by the fast pace, blocked 4-2, closed off strongly when clear, just beaten by a nose in 2nd.
Bumped start, pushed early, 6Ls off the leaders 3 wide, helped by the fast tempo, held up 400M, made ground steadily when clear and grabbed 3rd.
Eased back, 6Ls off the leaders, suited by the fast pace, trapped 4 wide throughout and lost too much ground, progressed steadily 250M.
Slow away, eased back, 6Ls off the leaders 2 wide, favoured by the fast pace, lacked room 4-2, made ground when clear, run ended 100M.
Awkward away, behind midfield, 4.5Ls off the leaders on the rails, benefited by the fast pace, made some ground in straight.
Prominent, 1.5Ls off the leaders 2 wide, not suited by the fast tempo, ran on until 200M flattened.
Very slow away, at rear, 7.5Ls off the leaders, favoured by the fast pace, but raced 3-4 wide throughout, made very late ground from 100M.
Hard ridden to share the lead at fast early sectionals 2 wide, out of fuel 300M.
Eased to sit in midfield, 3Ls behind fast pace 2 wide, ran on until 200M flattened.
Hard ridden to keep up in midfield, 3Ls off the fast pace along the fence, flattened 200M.
Pushed to obtain the box seat, not suited by the fast pace, emptied 300M.
Hard ridden to hold the rail and shared the lead at fast sectionals, weakened quickly 400M.
Hard ridden early, trapped 3 wide throughout in midfield, 3Ls off the fast pace, lost too much ground at bends, soon dropped off 400M.
Broke well from gate one and shared the lead on rails, quickened clear 300m, kept on strongly to hold off challenger.
Reasonable start, allowed to ease 7-8Ls behind the leader, kicked strongly down centre of home straight, finished soundly to snare 2nd.
Jumped fastest and sat handy on the rails, shifted wider and launched a challenge early in straight, looked possible to pick up winner but bit one-paced from 100m, lost 2nd in the final stride.
Out in line, held a fence position within striking distance from the leader, made up ground steadily from 300m but never really troubled the principals.
Out in line but slow into strides, caught up steadily and ended up in one out one back spot, kept on well until flattened 100m out.
Eased back 10Ls off the pace 4-wide without cover, crept closer at straightening, dashed well 350m but offered little threat to the placegetters.
No early speed, sat 9Ls off the pace 2-wide with cover, patiently ridden until 400m, made up considerable ground down centre of the home straightdown centre of the home straight.
Slow to begin, urged to sit 11Ls back in the rear, under pressure and lost touch from 800m, shifted to the inner for for home and showed good turn of foot late from 250m, finished off well.
Drifted back and found a fence spot 7Ls off the pace, urged to hold his position rounding bend, passed only tired runners in the home straight.
Jumped fast, sat 2Ls behind the leader, 2-wide with cover, travelled well until weakened passing 350m.
Slow to begin, restrained 9Ls off pace 2-wide with cover, responded only fairly when asked for efforts from 450m, passed only tired runners in the straight.
Jumped fast but taken 4Ls off the pace 2-wide, overraced in the early stages until 600m, swung widest for home, just one-paced, got tired passing 200m.
Prominently placed 3Ls behind the leader, shifted wider for home, could not keep up passing 350m, soon weakened.
Began bit slowly, urged to chase leader 4-wide without cover, eased 1L off pace near 800m, no extra early in straight, retreated passing 400m. (Mucus.)

Unable to slot in from a wide draw and was forced wide behind mid-division throughout, quickened impressively from off the pace inside 400M, kept on strongly in late stages to pick off the race leader 2 strides before the line.
Held up behind midfield about 4 back on the fence, into clear 300M and was produced with every chance, briefly led 100M but was nailed by the winner close home.
Always in touch 2Ls behind leader, accelerated well once driven and quickly moved to the front passing 250M, couldn't match strides with the first two but found enough to hold on for 3rd.
Slowly away then checked shortly after jump, ended up in last about 7Ls behind leader, fanned 3-wide into straight, made good headway final 400M to finish closest on the line.
Switched off towards the back and waited with till 450M, was momentarily steadied near 300M before staying on to go 5th just before the line.
Pushed along to a prominent position just behind leader, had every chance turning in, kept battling towards the finish but no extra pace to seriously challenge.
Never far off the pace but raced 3-wide without cover, briefly threatened early stretch but unable to sustain run inside 200M.
Held up towards the tail of the field in early and middle stages, saved ground on the inside, made some headway inside 400M without reaching the leaders.
Up with the early pace but taken back to midfield passing 1200M, 3-wide turning for home, lacked response and only kept on at the same pace.
Never better than midfield, shifted away from fence to challenge passing 400M, lacked a turn of foot and found no extra in late stages.
Proved difficult to settle in midfield, driven inside 400M but no progress.
Quickly into stride, soon crossed to the fence and led them at even tempo, headed 250M then weakened rapidly towards the line.
Awkwardly away, driven along to race in a handy 3rd but inclined to hang out in middle stages, didn't pick up on straightening, eased when beaten near 150M.
Settled 2-wide behind midfield, weakened rapidly turning into straight, heavily eased. (Heart Irregularity.)
Jumped in line, slow into strides, urged to lead on rails from 1000m, 1L clear at the 200m, just did enough to hold off late challenger.
Broke well, sat 3Ls behinds the leader 2-wide, bit overraced near 800m, obtained clear run and made ground down centre of the home straight, hung in, just late.
Jumped 2nd last, sat 6Ls off pace at the rear, closed sharply final 350m, squeezed through a narrow gap 100m and made remarkable ground for 3rd.
Out well and soon occupied a fence position within striking distance from the leader, closed nicely from 350m, lost 3rd in the final stride.
Easily ran up to sit 2Ls off the pace 2-wide with cover, made ground steadily from 350m, checked near the line and just lost 3rd.
Broke well, urged to take the one out one back spot, had every chance, held the 2nd until flattened near 100m.
Out in line, eased rearward 5Ls off pace 3-wide with cover, shifted widest for home, made substantial ground down centre of home straight but never really troubled the placegetters.
Taken back from widest alley in rear division, 7Ls off the speed, well back to bend, made some late progress without threatening.
Broke fastest, restrained 2Ls behind the leader 3-wide no cover, kept on well and looked possible to place until got tired passing 150m, badly checked 80m.
Urged to take the box-seat behind the leader, travelled well rounding bend, gave very limited respond when asked for efforts from 400m and emptied 200m.
Awkward start, settled 5Ls off pace 2-wide with cover, badly held up early in straight and blundered at the 300m, clear from 200m and passed the tired runners.
Last to jump, sat 6Ls off the speed, stayed rear division throughout, made no impression.
Reasonably jumped, sat 4Ls behind the leader 4-wide, no cover from 800m, weakened sharply passing 300m.
Sat 4Ls behind the pace 3-wide with cover, struggled from the top of home straight, was well beaten 300m.
Gradually improved to close-up position, restrained to 2Ls back in 4th approaching home bend, made modest headway in straight to just get up on line.
Close up, travelled outside leader most of way before taking over turning in, soon drew 1L clear over 200 M out, but only to be pipped at post.
Settled one back in 3rd on rails, came under pressure after straightening, fought on steadily without threatening.
Never far off in 5th far side and around the bend, baulked and forced to switch in for a run 300 M out, kept on steadily without quickening.
Began with others, settled in midfield, produced some late impression closing stages. (Bled.)
Settled towards the rear, wide into straight, ran on steadily to be nearest at finish.
Gradually crossed to take up running, led the field to until headed into straight, weakened under pressure.
Settled on rails in midfield, ran home one-paced.
Settled in last few, saved ground turning in, made no impression in straight.
Settled just worse than midfield, shuffled backward turning in, no response under pressure.
Began with others from the wide draw, soon taken back to race in rear of field, saved ground turning for home, made no further impression. (Tendon injury.)
Drawn wide, began with others, settled 3Ls back in 6th, faded gradually after straightening.
Soon taken well behind, trailed the field into straight, did nothing in straight.
Settled on rails in midfield, switched out for a run turning in, made steady progress down straight to assert authority close to home.

Began fairly from the widest barrier, remained wide without cover in forward of midfield, commenced move approaching home turn, fought on doggedly to hold every chance only to be outlasted close to home.
Began from a high draw, niggled at to gain prominent spot outside leader far side, remained same into straight, shaken up to tackle leaders passing 300 M but failed to respond to rider's urge.
Began with others, gradually crossed to lead, held narrow advantage into straight, unable to sustain effort and headed 100 M out.
Began moderately, raced behind midfield, inconvenienced over 300 M out but finishing off race well, did best work late.
Soon taken back to race in rear, ran home well down centre of straight to be nearest at finish.
Settled in midfield, similar turning for home, fought on steadily without threatening.
Began sharply, settled one back in 3rd on rails, did not find any room in box-seat run throughout straight, not tested.
Settled well behind, trailed the field to straight, ran on past well beaten horses closing stages.
Gradually came across to race 2-wide in coveted 4th position, found no response after straightening, ran home one-paced.
Began fairly, raced wide in midfield, ran home steadily without making any serious impression. (Tactic questioned.)
Raced keenly in last few far side, baulked behind runners early in straight, kept on at the one pace to finish.
Settled in forward of midfield, baulked early in straight, found nil under pressure passing 300 M.

Comment: Comments on Running is not available for this race.
Positioned behind midfield and travelled strongly throughout, picked up in good style entering home straight, swept to the front near 100 M and drew well clear at the finish.
Fractious in stalls and slow to begin, held inside running in midfield, picked up well to go 2nd final 50 M but made little impression on the winner.
In the group chasing leaders early, strode forward to press the lead passing 600 M, led with 200 M to go, kept on but not pace of the first two in late stages.
Restrained after jump, settled in midfield about 3Ls behind leaders, briefly threatened with a promising looking run early straight but turned one pace final 150 M.
Taken back from a wide draw, soon detached from the field and had to be niggled along to stay in touch, switched widest to challenge from 350 M, ran on well but was left with too much to do.
Forced the early pace then eased back to sit behind leaders, had his chance but lacked pace to seriously challenge.
Made use early and vied for lead till 600 M, held slender advantage turning in, headed 200 M and could find no extra in late stages.
Not hurried after the jump and settled towards the rear 6Ls off the pace, kept on same speed in straight under maximum pressure, never factored.
Driven forward in early stages but unable to overcome the wide barrier, 5-wide throughout and covered more ground than others, found nothing on straightening and soon dropped out of contention.
Ordinary jump but soon pushed to a rail position just off the lead, shuffled back to midfield approaching the turn, couldn't go with them as the race got serious, eased close home.
Never far off in chasing group just behind leaders, caught 4-wide without cover from 700 M, driven approaching 400 M but no progress, dropped out gradually.
Went to the front as expected but was caught wide until 600 M, outpaced making the final turn then weakened rapidly passing 200 M.
Tracked the leader, sitting to its outside, about 3 parts of a length back. Wound up fully approaching the 100 M and responded to heavy pressure to snatch victory close to home.
Made the running along the rail. Challenged at the 100 M and fought on strongly to be narrowly beaten.
Prominently positioned, 1 off with cover. Chased gamely in the straight.
Raced midfield 3 deep with cover. Ran on soundly.
Raced on the speed, 3 deep without cover. Hung out on the circle, plodded to the line.
Missed the start then was ridden along to go forward settling around midfield, 4 deep with cover. Worked home adequately in the straight.
Slow to begin settling in last position, 1 off with cover. Made satisfactory ground through the field in the final stretch.
Took up a forward position, however proved difficult to settle when being steadied and was unable to obtain a position with cover, traveling 4-wide. Not likely.
Couldn't go the early speed of the race settling with the backmakers along the fence. Kept on somewhat one paced over the final stages.
Travelled with the rear division, 2-wide with cover. Struggled in the straight.
Showed some early speed to camp behind the leader along the fence. Faded quickly after turning for home.
Settled towards the rear, 3-wide with cover. Was a beaten horse near the 400 M.

Took hold at midfield after start. Then was allowed to stride forward outside field making the first turn. Led on fence from 700 M and was 2Ls clear into home straight. Kept on to hold off the runner up.
Better than midfield on fence and proved difficult to settle through to the home turn. Peeled out and was 3Ls down on straightening. Chased well to line.

Jumped well. Ridden vigorously early from high draw to cut across first turn. Never far off the pace in a 2-wide position back straight. Kept giving in the final stretch but failed to match on terms with the front pair.
Pressed early and led first turn. Elected to sit behind the pace on fence from 800 M. 2Ls adrift turning in. Ran on but managed only to hold 4th narrowly.
Dropped to rear from high draw. Improved slightly in a 3-wide position passing 800 M. Swung wide and was 6Ls off on straightening. Covered good ground in the straight and nearly made frame.
Quickly into stride. Took seat ahead of midfield in a 3-wide position from 1000 M. Lay out making the home turn and was 4Ls down into home straight. One-paced to conclude.
Urged early to occupy a midfield spot one-off the fence. Hard ridden from 500 M and was 5Ls behind the pace leaving the bend. Never nearer.
Travelled along the fence at midfield through to the home straight. No response under pressure.
At rear on fence early and middle stages. Beat only tired runners home.
2-wide towards rear throughout. Never likely.
Always at rear. No impression.

Urged to obtain a 2-wide position 3Ls behind the leader, little bit overraced passing 1000 M, responded well when asked for efforts 400 M, took the lead 150 M out, did enough to hold off the challenger.

Out in line, taken to one from rear 8 to 9Ls off the speed, relaxed and travelled well throughout, urged along at straightening and swung widest for home, dashed well under the whip from 200 M to take 2nd.
Standard jump, restrained to a fence position 5Ls off the pace, shifted wide for home, responded well when clear bit late near 200 M out to finish 3rd.

Slow into stride, pushed hard and found the fence at 1300 M, two from rear 7Ls behind the leader, responded slowly when asked for efforts from 400 M, clicked into gear 200 M and made up ground strongly, just lost 3rd.
Jumped fairly from the outside draw, settled 4Ls off the pace 2-wide with cover, shifted wider for home, looked possible for a place passing 200 M, bit one-paced and missed out.

Jumped fast from its outside barrier, ended up in one out one back spot, hit the lead passing 400 M, looked possible to score but overhauled at 150 M, soon flattened, lost the place in the last few strides.
Slow to begin, taken back 6Ls off the pace 2-wide, made ground steadily down centre of the home straight from 300 M but never really threatened placegetters.
Box-seated just behind the leader, travelled nicely in early stages, held up early in straight, only one-paced when clear near 150 M.

Broke well, prominently sat 2Ls behind the pace, travelled keenly in middle stages, shifted wider at the 600 M to stride forward, contested the lead until run ended passing 200 M. (Lame in left front leg.)
Broke well, urged to hold the fence position 3 to 4Ls behind the leader, travelled well throughout, failed to quicken, proved beaten near 200 M.
Broker well, mustered fast to lead 1L, challenged near 400 M, weakened sharply passing 250, gave ground.
Slow to begin and muster, sat 11Ls off the pace, never competitive. (Lame in right hind leg.)
Standard jump, restrained 4Ls away from tearaway leaders on rails, crept closer rounding bend, shifted 3-wide and ran on strongly, hit the lead passing 250 M, drew clear with plenty in tank.
Bit slow to begin, settled cosily 7Ls behind tearaway leaders 2-wide, shifted to the inner for home, finished off well when clear at the 200 M, took 2nd passing 80 M.
Broke well, box-seated just behind the leader, travelled strongly after being urged at 1200 M, had every chance in the straight, failed to challenge winner and lost 2nd passing 100 M.
Awkwardly started, settled 9Ls off the pace 2-wide, shifted wide for home, made up some ground but never troubled the principals.

Bit slow to begin, allowed to drifted back 10Ls off the pace, found the fence at 1500 M, urged to hold the position in the middle stages, made ground steadily when clear near 200 M but failed to threaten placegetters.
Jumped well from the widest gate, urged to get across and lead, remained uncontested until 350 M, overhauled 300 M, flattened passing 150 M.
Bit slow to begin, settled 7Ls off the pace on rails, caused interference when swung wide for home, finished off fairly well until run ended 150 M out.
Slow to begin, settled last over 10Ls away, was urged along to stay in touch, only passed the tired runners in straight.
Taken back one from the rear, 10Ls behind the speed, gave very limited responded when asked for efforts in the home straight.
Jumped and mustered well, restrained at the one out one back position, struggled turning into the home straight, weakened passing 300 M.

Placing: FE
Comment: Out in line, settled 5 to 6Ls off the pace 2-wide, travelled well until lost its rider at the home turn.

Placing: FE
Comment: Jumped fast, urged to sit 8 to 9Ls off the pace 3-wide with no cover, crept closer rounding bend, lost its rider at the home turn.
Hard ridden to take the rail and led by 1L at advantageous slow sectionals, made all without much threats.
Settled in front of midfield along the fence, 2Ls off the very slow pace, swept forward 2-wide 600 M to make run, little dash 200 M and finished 2nd.
Pushed to sit in midfield along the rails, 3-1/2Ls off the leader, harmed by the very slow pace, dashed strongly 250 M and grabbed 3rd.
Pushed to cross in front and occupied the box seat, raced very keenly, checked 400 M, not suited by the very slow tempo, just held ground in straight.
Eased to rear and took rail, 6-1/2Ls off the leader, swept forward 3-wide round the home bend, dashed strongly 200 M despite harmed by the very slow pace.
Eased to rear, 7Ls off the leader 2 to 3-wide, made early move from 700 M, dashed well 300 M despite harmed by the very slow pace, run ended 100 M.
Eased to sit behind the front runners, 2-1/2Ls off the leader 2 to 3-wide, not suited by the very slow tempo, just held ground in straight.
Behind midfield, 5Ls off the leader along the fence, harmed by the very slow pace, dashed well in straight, lacked room 200 M.
Midfield, 4Ls off the leader 2 to 3-wide, not suited by the very slow pace, dashed fairly in final stages.
Hard ridden forward, 1L off the leader 2-wide, helped by the very slow tempo, flattened 200 M.
Eased to rear for cover, 6-1/2Ls off the leader 2 to 3-wide, harmed by the very slow pace, little dash 100 M.
Eased back, harmed by the very slow pace, never competitive, tailed out.
Broke well from gate 1, settled cosily 2Ls behind the speed, shifted wider for home, clear at the top of the home straight, kicked strongly and drew clear passing 200 M, impressive.
Out in line, prominently settled 4Ls behind the leader, made ground strongly from 200 M but never really threatened the winner.
Jumped well from the widest gate, pushed hard along to lead and found the fence at 800 M, reeled in by the winner 300 M out but kept on well enough for 3rd.
Jumped fastest, pushed along and soon occupied a fence positioned just behind the leader, responded well when asked for efforts from 300 M, fought hard for a place from 200 M, just missed out.
Broke well, prominently sat within striking distance from the leader, shifted wider for home, fought hard in straight but just missed out a place.
Settled 4 to 5Ls behind the leader, 3-wide with no cover, moved closer from 600 M, caught 4-wide at the final turn, kept on fairly well but not enough for a place.
Out well, sat in midfield 2-wide with cover, swung wide for home, gave limited response when asked for efforts from 300 M.
Jumped well, taken back three from the rear 5Ls off pace, 2-wide with cover, remained one-paced in the home straight.
Out in line, checked badly near 1000 M, settled 6Ls behind the leader on rails, failed to make up ground in straight.
Taken to the rear from its awkward draw, found the fence near 700 M out, was checked at the home turn, made no impression in straight.
Caught 4-wide with no cover in midfield, sent forward to join the lead passing 700 M, weakened sharply early in straight.
Taken back to the rear from it outside barrier, 3-wide with cover, lacked a turn of foot in straight, never likely.
Restrained to a position ahead of midfield, moved to a striking position passing 400 M, quickened well to take it up nearing 150 M and held on to the lead determinedly.
Travelled well in mid-division, switched away from fence to improve passing 450 M, strongly challenged inside 300 M and pushed the winner all the way to the line.
Assumed a rail position in midfield, briefly held up rounding the home turn, picked up strongly in straight to go 3rd inside 100 M.
Settled 2-wide behind mid-division and had an uneventful trip throughout, stayed on well final 250 M to finish nearest on the line.

Not hurried in early stages, settled towards the rear 7 to 8Ls off the pace, driven from 400 M, ran on strongly down the centre of the track but was never getting there in time. (Jockey questioned re his riding tactics.)
Up with the early pace and positioned one out one back making the home turn, had his chance but was outpaced final 200 M.
Quickly into stride, obtained a spot on the fence and led them steadily, headed inside 200 M then weakened rapidly towards the finish.
Couldn't muster despite ridden along and soon detached from the field, over 10Ls to make up passing 400 M, stayed on to go past beaten rivals.
Settled 2-wide in midfield 4Ls off leaders, came widest into straight but not picked up, eased. (Jockey questioned re his riding in straight.)
With leaders early but outpaced approaching home turn, struggled to keep up and soon behind inside 250 M.
With leaders but trapped 3-wide throughout, was very awkward rounding the home bend and appeared to be badly tired entering the straight, eased.

In touch, settled 2-wide in the group chasing leaders, responded well and swept to the front near 300M, drew well clear from the rest and won with tremendous amount of ease.
Settled in 5th in front of midfield and had an uneventful trip, took time to get going in straight, no chance with the runaway winner but ran on ok to reel in the 3rd inside 100M.
Broke well, restrained to midfield 4-5Ls off the pace, stayed on from 300M without threatening the runaway winner, lost 2nd 75M from home.
In chasing group just off leaders, always in touch, was produced with every chance in straight, couldn't find the pace to challenge and looked very laboured towards the line.
Travelled 2-wide behind mid-division, angled out for a clear run near 400M, stayed on but was never threatening.
Patiently ridden behind midfield, switched out for a run inside 450M, ran on only fairly and found no extra in late stages.
Pressed the lead 2-wide down the back straight, plodded on to 200M then weakened towards the finish.
Held up towards the rear and waited with till 450M, kept on same pace only, never a factor.
Assumed a midfield position along the rails, 4Ls off the lead turning for home, made no impression when asked for an effort and weakened badly in late stages.
Never better than midfield and not picking up when asked on straightening. (Retired after race.)
Went forward as expected and led steadily on fence, headed inside 300M and weakened rapidly final 150M. (Retired after race.)
Taken across behind runners from draw 13 and over 10Ls back in last, driven but no progress inside 450M, eased.
Towards the rear and had a ground saving trip throughout but struggled to go with them passing 500M, finished tailed out.

Placing: UR
Comment: Reared at the start, shifted in abruptly and lost rider.
Bumped at the start then rallied nicely to stroll forward and cross to settle as equal leader near the 800m, showed good acceleration to draw a margin over the final stages.

Wasn't the best into stride settling well off the speed towards the middle, but soon got onto the bridle and travelled easily to race with the principals. Vied for the lead joining the course proper and kept on soundly.
Railed up early from the outside alley to take up leading duties. Dueled as the front runner after the 800m, maintained a sound gallop right to the finishing post.
Raced on the outside fence, midfield. kept on at the same speed in the latter stages.
Was checked about a furlong after the jump settling slightly worse than midfield. Made steady ground over the concluding stages.
Settled midfield towards the centre of the course. Was under full pressure near the 300m, but gave little response.
Settled towards the outside fence close to the pace with cover. Made little impression over the final stages. Vet reported that the horse returned with blood inn the trachea.
Parked behind the leaders early toward the grandstand side. Couldn't quicken with the front trio and only battled to the winning post.
Positioned close to midfield along the centre of the track. Failed to quicken at any stage.
Settled close to midfield. Gave little at the business end weakening well before the finish line.
Began awkwardly, then was steadied soon after the start and shifted in, taking up a position behind the field towards the rear. Only plodded to the line.
Settled in a handy position just off the leaders. Had every chance and conceded ground in the run to the post.
Settled in last position with cover. Struggled in the final stages.
Camped behind the speed with cover. Commenced to be ridden along near the 400m and was a beaten horse soon after.

Last out and was taken to rail behind runners. Moved up to race behind midfield making the home turn. 4Ls down on straightening. Not clearest until final furlong. Rallied on final 100M to charge down rivals.

Soon in front but elected to take seat behind the leader. Attacked the lead in the home straight and hit front 150M. Kept on but failed to fend off the winner closing stages. Barely held 2nd at finish.
2-wide at midfield through to the home turn and was 4Ls away leaving the bend. Finished off strongly and nearly snatched 2nd.
3-wide ahead of midfield through to the home turn and was 3Ls off entering the final stretch. Kept giving to make frame but was firmly put aside by the front trio closing stages.
At rear near the fence early. Pressed from 650M. Peeled out and was 5Ls behind the leader entering the home straight. Ran on but not threatening.
Hard ridden early to hold lead on fence. Maintained a 1L gap until headed 200M. Plugged on.
Urged always but trapped 4-wide towards rear through to the home straight. Covered some ground thereafter to beat tired runners.
Slow to begin and was shaken early. Sat 3-wide behind midfield passing 1000M. Improved well top of home straight and was only 1L behind leaders near 200M. Failed to follow through.
Travelled wide and without cover at midfield. Got closer approaching the home straight but failed to turn up a notch passing 300M. Weakened 150M.
Raced within 2Ls of the pace in a 2-wide position through to the home straight. Found nothing under pressure.
Always at rear. No impression.
Urged to hold a handy position on fence through to the home straight. Failed to quicken when asked.
No early speed, sat rearward 6-7Ls behind the lead, crept closer down the outside in the back straight, swung widest for home, good turn of foot final 350m, hit the lead in the last stride.

Jumped fastest from gate one and pressed on to lead, opened up a 3Ls gap in the back straight, steadied to reserve stamina turning for home, kept on well and looked likely to score, just headed in the last stride.
Out in line but showed no early speed, held midfield along the fence, 5-6Ls behind the leader, shifted wider for home, ran on steadily in straight, just did enough for 3rd.
Standard jump, prominently placed on rails within striking distance from the leader, had every chance in home straight, responded fairly well when clear passing 200m, lost 3rd in the last stride.
Broke well, restrained 4-5Ls off the speed, 2-wide with cover, niggled long round bend, made ground steadily when asked near 350m, turned one-paced final 100m, just lost a place.
Taken back at start to find the fence, rearward 7-8Ls off the speed, urged along rounding bend, swung widest for home, did make up some ground but insufficient for a place.
Prominently sat just behind the leader, travelled nicely throughout, attempted to challenge the leader passing 400m, could not kept up near 150m and soon got tired.
Broke well from the wide draw, sat 3-4Ls off the pace, 3-wide with no cover in the back straight, had his chance but could not find extra when asked passing 400m, flattened at 200m.
Out in line, held midfield 3-wide with cover, shifted wide for home, gave very limited response when asked for efforts final 350 m.
Jumped fastest, settled in a fence position 5-6Ls behind the leader, struggled rounding bend, proven beaten early in home straight.
Slow to begin and caught very wide entering the back straight, urged to catch up 3Ls off the pace, caught 4-wide with no cover, got tired passing 300m.
Out in line, settled 6Ls behind the speed 2-wide with cover, bit outpaced rounding bend, no dash in home straight, proven beaten passing 300m.
Blundered badly at start, lost touch when rider was unbalanced, caught up 11Ls off the pace in back straight, swung wide for home, lacked turn of foot when asked final 400m.
Failed to muster early speed, drifted back to one from the rear, 9Ls off pace 4-wide with cover, yielded ground rounding bend, proven beaten early in the home straight.
Broke well, taken back and found a 3-wide spot with cover 4Ls behind leaders, urged along turning for home, finished off strongly down centre of the home from 350m, took the lead in the final stride.

Jumped fast and sat handily to the leader, travelled strongly in middle stages, shifted wider for home, responded well when asked for efforts from 400m, briefly led near 100m, just caught by the winner in the final stride.

Broke well, sat prominently within striking distance from leaders, 3-wide with cover, difficult to settle in early and middle stages, swung widest for home, had every chance and looked possible near 200m, lacked decisive kick final 100m.

Out in line, urged to occupy a 2-wide position in midfield, found the fence near 800m, shifted wider to obtain clear run passing 400m, responded only fairly until really started making up ground from 150m.
Broke fastest, urged to get across in front, ended up sharing lead one off, made the final turn bit awkwardly, kept on well until overhauled at 150m, soon flattened.
Slow to begin, mustered fast and ended up sharing lead on rails, travelled well rounding bend, kept on fairly when asked for efforts from 350m, overhauled and flattened passing 150m.
Bumped start and slow into stride, pushed to track leader 3-wide, with no cover, kept on until got tired passing 150m.
Out in line but caught very wide early, eased to mid-division near 1100m, 4-wide with cover, gave limited response when asked for efforts from 400m, no extra from 150m.

Slow to begin, eased rearward to find the fence, 7Ls behind the speed, patiently ridden until entering the home straight, improved along the inner, shifted out to avoid heels near 200m, finished off fairly well.
Crowded start and lost ground, soon improved along the rails sitting just behind the leaders, held up early in straight, lacked a kick and got tired passed 200m.
Very slow to begin, pushed hard to catch up 8Ls off the pace at rear, shifted wider for home, passed only tired runners in the home straight.
Out in line but slow mustering, drifted rearward 5-6Ls off pace, niggled along to hold the position near 1000m, started started struggling from the top of the straight, dropped off 250m.
Jumped bit awkwardly, showed no early speed, two from the rear 6Ls behind the speed, gave very limited response when when asked for efforts from 450m, proven beaten at 300m.
Jumped fast from its outside barrier, raced keenly and sat close up 4-wide with no cover, got tired and gave ground early from 700m, tailed out.
Pushed to secure the box seat, not suited by the fast early tempo but helped by the rail trip, closed the race off strongly 300M to win.
Awkward away, settled in midfield along the rails, 4.5Ls off the leaders, tracked the winner throughout, favoured by the fast pace, progressed steadily 300M to take 2nd.
Awkward away, settled at back, 7Ls off the leaders along the fence, benefited by the fast tempo and the rail trip, lacked room 400M, made ground steadily when clear and got 3rd.
Eased back, 8.5Ls off the leaders 2 wide, favoured by the fast pace, held up 4-2, progressed steadily when clear but not good enough to grab a place.
Took rail and shared the lead at fast early sectionals, under pressure throughout and used up too much fuel, hung on until 200M overhauled and flattened.
In front of midfield, 2.5Ls behind the fast pace, trapped 3-4 wide throughout and lost too much ground, ran no well until 200M flattened.
Eased to rear, more than 10Ls off the leaders on the fence, helped by the fast pace, raced flat until 200M made some minor ground.
Pushed to obtain a prominent spot, 1.5Ls off the leaders 2 wide, not suited by the fast pace, weakened 200M.
Hard ridden to sit in front of midfield, 3.5Ls off the leaders 2 wide, suited by the fast tempo, flattened 200M.
Pushed forward, 1L off the leaders, trapped 3 wide throughout and lost ground, harmed by the fast pace, weakened 250M.
Eased to sit in midfield, 5Ls off the leaders 2-3 wide, benefited by the fast tempo, ran on fairly.
Eased back, 8.5Ls off the leaders, trapped 3-4 wide throughout and lost ground, helped by the fast pace, no turn of foot in straight.
Eased back, 7Ls off the leaders 2-3 wide, favoured by the fast tempo, however never progress.
Pushed forward to cross, shared the lead 2 wide at fast sectionals, soon dropped off 300M.
Broke well, handily sat just behind the leader, showed good turn of foot when asked for efforts near 400m, hit the lead 200m, scored comfortably.
Standard jump, soon settled in rear 2-3Ls off pace shifting towards stand rails, ran on well when clear 300m out, finished off very strongly for 2nd.
Drawn on the farside but soon moved across to share the lead, travelled strongly in early stages, kept on well when asked for efforts from 400m, overhauled 200m, lost 2nd in last few strides.
Gradually taken back to midfield near the stand rails, made ground steadily when asked passing 400m but failed to find extra to challenge the top three in the concluding stages.
Jumped fast, soon found the stand rails sitting just behind the leader, tended to lay in when asked to improve through a narrow gap, ran home well when clear late at 150m.
Jumped fastest, pulled his way up to share the lead on the stand rails, travelled well until overhauled by the winner passing 250m, did not respond when asked for efforts, so flattened. (Mucus)

Broke well, held back to race in midfield within 2Ls off the pace, lost cover when the leader shifted out near 600m, gave limited response when asked for efforts 350m out, yielded ground under pressure.
Held midfield to 300m, failed to quicken under pressure, showed no impression.
Out in line, settled midfield down the centre of the track in early stages, hung in under the whip passing 400m, soon dropped out.
Started awkwardly losing ground, taken back close to the rear for cover after beginning from the innermost draw, tended to lay in final 400m, never seen with a chance.
Settled handily in 3rd 3-4Ls behind the runaway leader, quickened well to strike the front nearing 100M, drew nicely clear at the finish and won this in fine style.

Ordinary start, went forward and soon led, kicked 4Ls clear over the home turn, kept on well only to be headed 100M, faded in late stages but managed to cling on for 2nd. (Jockey questioned regarding riding tactics.)
Taken across behind runners from draw 12, settled in last but not hurried, swung wide into straight and picked up strongly from off the pace to finish 3rd. (Jockey dropped whip 250M.)
Taken back from a wide draw, settled 7-8Ls back towards the fence, steadied near 300M then ran on strongly to finish 4th, never nearer.
Not far off from leaders in early stages but got outpaced making the final turn, made some headway inside 250M despite hanging in.
Quickly into stride, chased leader in 2nd place, weakened inside 200M and found no extra close home.
Slow to begin, improved to a midfield position along the rail, couldn't find another gear and remained at the one-pace throughout the straight.
Dropped back to the rear after an even break, swung widest for home and couldn't quicken under pressure.
Raced 2-wide behind mid-division but proved very difficult to settle, had a clear run coming off the bend but found disappointingly little in the finish.
Broke well but was soon restrained, settled behind midfield 3-wide, hard driven inside 350M but couldn't muster and kept on at the same pace to the line.
Raced 3-wide throughout in midpack, driven but no progress inside 300M, eased when no chance.
Not far off the lead in early stages, checked near 500M and shuffled back, didn't pick up coming off the bend and never any impression.

Sat cosily 5Ls behind the leader 2-wide, shifted to inner in search of clear run early in home straight, dashed well under hands and heels riding when found room near 250m, hit the lead 100m, flew home with some in tank.

Broke well, prominently placed within striking distance from the leader, shifted wide for home, responded well when asked for efforts passing 400m, briefly led near 200m but soon reeled in by the winner.
Broke well from gate one, handily placed 1-2Ls behind the leader, obtained clear run passing 400m and finished off well for 3rd, pleasing debut.
Jumped fast, urged along to track the pacemaker, one off with cover, had every chance in home straight, lacked a strong kick to contest the lead, turned one-paced passing 200m.

Gradually taken back form the widest draw, sat last 9Ls off the pace with cover, patiently ridden until entering the home straight, dashed well under hands and heels riding from 400m but never really troubled the principals.
Out in line, urged to share the lead in a one-off position, kept on fighting until overhauled passing 200m, outpaced gradually.
Jumped fastest from its awkward barrier, allowed to ease for cover in mid-division, shifted wider from 600m, had his chance in the home straight but could not find the extra to challenge seriously.
Slowest to begin, urged to catch up 4Ls off the pacesetter 3-wide with cover, gave limited response when asked for effort final 350m.
Taken back from wide gate and keen initially, always rearward, about 6Ls off the pace last turn, passed only the tired runners in home straight.
Restrained rearward 6Ls behind the leader, 3-wide with cover, travelled keenly in early and middle stages, failed to find extra to make up ground in home straight.
Taken back to the rear from wide gate, 7-8Ls off the pace on rails, passed only the tired runners in home straight.
Jumped bit slowly, urged to hold a fence position 5Ls behind the pace, on heels at 300m, lost further ground in straight.
Mustering fast to lead on the rails, joined from 800m out, got exhausted early in straight, gave ground rapidly.
Out slowly, sat three from the rear on the rails, struggled rounding bend, gave no response when asked for efforts from 400m, weakened and tailed out.
Jumped nicely, took ideal spot on leaders back, used nothing in run, took inside runs turning in, dashed away final 200 M to win comprehensively.
Pressed on from a wide gate, posted 3 wide without cover 2Ls off speed, kept improving on bend, shared lead at 300 M, kept on well after hard run but outclassed final furlong.
Taken back from a wide alley, raced 3 wide with cover at tail, best part of 8Ls down to bend, still last turning, closed off well late making good ground for 3rd.
Out with first few, ended up 3 to 4Ls back in running line behind pace, even run to bend, just held ground in straight and just missed 3rd.
Restrained from an awkward draw, raced 5 to 6Ls away on rails, saved ground turning, made some progress late without threatening.
Well enough away, ended up in nice position 1 out 1 back, OK trip to bend, didn't let down in straight and just kept on at same tempo.
No early speed, raced behind midfield 6Ls or so off top end, 2 wide to bend, didn't have dash to factor and just kept on at same speed.
Showed good pace to sit on speed, outside leader throughout, headed up on turning, under pressure by 250 M and unable to continue effort, dropped out.
Faded back from the widest gate, 3 wide behind midfield throughout, set a task still 7Ls down to bend, passed a couple of tiring horses late.
Began well, went on to take up running, set solid sections in front with pressure from outside horse, struggling passing 300 M, didn't respond and gradually weakened.
Positioned 3 wide just worse than midfield, 5 to 6Ls down throughout, had come to bend, checked at 400 M, not sighted in straight.
Not much early pace, soon at rear, 7 to 8Ls back in 2 wide line, still well back to turn, only battled home passing beaten brigade.
Even jump, had easy time in midfield 3 to 4Ls back on rails, used nothing to turn, offered little in run to line. Poor.
Moderate beginning, landed 3 wide in midfield with cover 3 to 4Ls away to bend, gradually faded out in straight.

Tucked in behind horses from draw 12 and had a smooth run at the back of the field, had 7Ls to make up at top of the straight but really motored final 250 M defying his top weight to win this in fine style.

Forced wide early then crossed to lead on fence near 1200 M, set even tempo up front and kicked 2Ls clear off the bend, stuck on doggedly and looked likely to win before the winner came up a few strides before the line.

Quickly into stride, settled handily along the fence one back from leader, poised to strike passing 400 M, chased leader in straight but had no answer when the eventual winner flew past in final stages.
Up with the early pace, positioned in 5th just off leaders down the back straight, had to switch wide to avoid beaten runners over the home bend, battled on till finding no extra in late stages.
Angled in after the start to be 2-wide behind midpack, made steady progress turning into straight and finished never nearer.
Obtained a rail spot behind midfield, 6Ls down turning for home, headway inside 300 M but never looked likely.
Awkwardly away, travelled towards the rear 8Ls off the pace, driven approaching 400 M, made some progress down the outside without threatening the principals.
Well enough away, restrained to a 2-wide spot in mid-division, switched wide to make his challenge passing 400 M, ran on only fairly and lacked the pace to be competitive inside 200 M.
Drawn on the inside but had to be hard driven early to hold a rail position ahead of midfield, moved up to 3rd nearing the top of straight, had his chance but found no extra final 150 M.
In the group chasing the leader, caught wide throughout and raced without cover down the back straight, struggled to keep up nearing 400 M, dropped out rapidly. (Unacceptable performance.)
Went forward on jumping from a wide barrier and tracked leader one out one back, outpaced over the final turn and weakened rapidly passing 400 M, eased. (Unacceptable performance.)
No early speed and soon ended up in the rear, didn't travel at all and was left behind making the home turn, tailed out. (Unacceptable performance.)
Settled 3 back the rail. Darted through to the inside on straightening and was never headed after hitting the front near the 200 M.
Camped midfield, 2-wide with cover. Rolled out on the home turn and dug deep to snare second close to home despite wanting to lay in early in the straight.
Handed up early and stalked the leader before peeling out near the 600 M and vying for the lead. Was in front at the furlong but was claimed soon after. Maintained a good gallop right to the wire.
Positioned midfield on the fence. Sought inside runs in the final stretch and made sound headway before peaking near the 100 M.

Settled handy to the leaders, 1 off without cover. Was carried out slightly passing the 600 M to race 2 to 3-wide on the circle, got a trail into the home turn but weakened on its effort after looming as a possible chance.
Raced worse than midfield, 2 deep with cover. Didn't make any impression in the run to the post.
From the outside barrier settled back in the event, 1 off with cover. Kept on one paced over the concluding stages.
Positioned with the backmakers on the paint. Never made any appreciable ground in the home straight.
Bounded in the air as the gates opened losing considerable ground settling behind midfield on the fence. Stayed to the inside in the straight, but failed to quicken and only battled to the finish.
Led along the fence for the majority of the race. Was challenged after the 500 M, gave little when asked for an effort turning for home.
Raced at the rear of the field, 3-wide with cover. Struggled in the run home.
Settled behind midfield, 3-wide without cover. Never likely.

Quickly into stride. Elected to sit within 2Ls of the speed near the fence until home straight. Finished off well and hit front 200 M. Seriously challenged near finish but hung on for a narrow victory.
2-wide behind midfield early and middle stages. 5Ls down on straightening. Made a strong run from 250 M. Just held by the winner.
Pressed early and soon led one-off the fence. Took box-seat from the Rock. Fought on but failed to fend off the front pair closing stages.

Taken to stay 2-wide towards rear from high draw early and middle stages. 6Ls away turning in. Launched attack top of home straight but was hampered near 200 M. Resumed well and was nearest at finish.

Soon in front rank but not sufficient speed to lead. Travelled 4-wide ahead of midfield first turn. Moved up gradually from 700 M and shifted 2-wide behind the speed turning in. Kept giving without seriously threatening.
Hard ridden outside the field after start. Eventually took lead on fence near the Rock. Maintained a 1L break turning into home. Headed passing 200 M and ran on.
Amongst leaders early. Steadied at 1100 M, then sat 2-wide ahead of midfield from 900 M. 4Ls off on straightening. Improved steadily thereafter.
Slow to begin and was urged early. Settled 4Ls behind the leader on fence through to the home straight. One-paced to conclude.
Began well but trapped 3-wide first turn. Sat 2-wide behind the pace passing 800 M. Came wide entering the home straight and ran on steadily.
Towards rear on fence through to the home straight. Plugged on.
Last out. Ridden passing 800 M to stay in touch. Detached making the home turn. Finished tailed out.

Out in line, soon occupied a 2-wide position in midfield, travelled comfortably throughout, shifted to the inner in search of clear run in home straight, dashed well and charged down rivals near finish.

Niggled along after fair start, prominently sat 2Ls behind the leaders 2-wide with cover, finished off well down centre of the home straight, looked possible to win passing 100 M while hanging in, caught by the winner near 50 M.

Jumped fairly, pushed hard along in early stages, ended up taking the box-seat just behind the leader, kept on well in home straight but laid in and out under pressure near 200 M, just did enough for 3rd.

Broke well from the high draw but mustered bit slowly, caught very wide at the first turn, ended up in one out one back spot, swung wide for home, kept on well in the straight led until grabbed passing 100 M, just lost a place.
Bit slow to begin, settled 7 to 8Ls behind the pace on rails, travelled nicely throughout, responded well when asked for efforts final 300 M, made up ground down centre of the home straight.
Broke fairly, urged to sit two from rear 2-wide with cover, niggled along rounding bend, made up some ground down centre of the home straight final 200 M, but never really troubled the principals.
Driven early to be fifth on the rails, prominently sat 2 to 3Ls off the speed, swung widest for home, responded only fairly when asked for efforts final 250 M, flattened 100 M out.
Started awkwardly, settled one from rear on rails 8 to 9Ls behind the pace, patiently ridden until turning for home, made little ground final 200 M.
Taken back from the widest stall, settled last 10Ls away, swung widest for home, never better than midfield.
Jumped fast from the wide gate, pressed on to lead 1L on rails, passed near 450 M, held ground until got tired 200 M.
Held a fence position in midfield, travelled comfortably until bit outpaced turning for home, gave no response when asked for efforts and dropped out early in straight.
Settled 2-wide 5 to 6Ls behind the leader, swung wide for home, clicked into gear final 300 M and hit the lead 200 M out, drew clear easily. Impressive.

Broke fairly, soon found a fence spot 6Ls off the leader, travelled strongly in early stages, responded well when asked for efforts final 300 M, squeezed through a gap 200 M out, just did enough for 2nd.
Jumped fairly, niggled along to sit one out one back, ran on to lead turning for home, overhauled by the winner 200 M but did keep on well itself, unlucky to lose 2nd.
Taken back from the wide stall, settled last down the back straight, niggled along from 500 M and swung widest for home, launched a strong kick final 250 M, just late for place.

Jumped fast, prominently sat within striking distance from the leader, 2-wide with cover in midfield, obtained clear run final 250 M, clicked into gear passing 200 M and looked likely for a place, just missed out.

Out in line, bit keen in early stage until box-seated behind the leader, travelled nicely throughout, kept on well and looked a place hope in home straight, matched the strides of the placegetters but just lacked the kick to beat them.
Jumped fast, prominently placed 2 to 3Ls behind the leader, had his chance but found too one-paced in home straight.

Taken back from the wide gate, ended up sitting two from rear, 7 to 8Ls off the speed 2-wide with cover, made ground steadily down centre of home straight final 200 M but offered little threat to the principals.

Lacked early speed, settled one from the rear on rails, approximately 8Ls behind the leader, urged along rounding bend, shifted wider for home, was crowded in concluding stages, made little ground final 200 M out.
Out in line, settled comfortably in midfield on the fence, tried to make up ground along the rails final 300 M, badly held up behind a tired runner, failed to pick up again when clear 100 M.
Mustered fast to lead 1L on rails, responded only fairly when asked for extra efforts final 300 M, overhauled passing 200 M, soon weakened sharply.
Jumped well from the widest gate but lacked early speed despite being pushed hard along, caught 3-wide with no cover 2 to 3Ls off the pace, failed to keep up and proven beaten passing 200 M.
Eased to rear for cover, 6Ls off the leader 2-wide, harmed by the very slow pace, demonstrated impressive finishing efforts 250 M, dominated 100 M.
Eased back, 4-1/2Ls off the leader 2 to 3-wide, dashed strongly 300 M despite harmed by the very slow pace, secured 2nd 100 M but no good enough to match the winner.
Crossed easily, took rail and lead early, eased to obtain the box seat, benefited by the very slow tempo, ran on well to the line for 3rd.
Trapped 3-wide throughout in front of midfield, 1-1/2Ls off the very slow pace, closed the race off strongly 300 M, emptied 150 M, lost too much ground at bends.
Midfield, 3Ls off the leader 2-wide, harmed by the very slow pace, lack room 300 M, little dash when clear.
Eased to sit behind the leaders, not suited by the very slow tempo, no turn of foot in straight.
Eased to rear, 7Ls off the leader on the rails, harmed by the very slow pace, little dash 200 M.
Eased to sit in midfield along the fence, 3Ls off the leader, not suited by the very slow tempo, no progress.
Eased back, 4-1/2Ls off the leader along the fence, harmed by the very slow pace, blocked most straight, checked 100 M, never tested, just ran on.
Slow away, hard ridden to sit outside the lead, enjoyed the very slow early sectionals, out of fuel 200 M.
Ease to sit behind the lead 2-wide early, went forward 1200 M to take rail and led by 1/2L at very slow sectionals, weakened 200 M.

Taken back from the wide gate, urged along to catch up 6Ls behind the leader after finding the fence, swung widest for home, launched a strong kick down the outside final 300 M, hit the lead in the final stride.

Out in line, shaken up to track the leaders one off, shifted wider for home, hung in but ran on well down centre of the straight, briefly led passing 100 M but grabbed by the winner in the final stride.
Started awkwardly, sat 3Ls behind the pace on rails, travelled satisfactorily throughout, dashed well when clear 300 M out, could out match the strides of the first two but kept on soundly for 3rd.

Started fairly, pressed on to share the lead along the rails passing 800 M, travelled nicely rounding bend, kept on well in the home straight, tackled inside 100 M, just lost a place in the final stride.
Broke well from the wide alley, urged along to share the lead, overhauled near 200 M, could not match the strides of the principal final 100 M.
Held midfield easily, 3Ls behind the leaders 2-wide, bumped at 300 M, made up ground steadily when clear 200 M but never really threatened the principals.
No Comments on Running information for this horse.
Jumped fast from the widest alley, sat 2 to 3Ls off the pace 3-wide, travelled keenly near 700 M, lost cover and caught 4-wide rounding bend, remained one-paced until flattened 150 M.
Jumped fastest, soon occupied a fence position 2Ls behind the leader, travelled satisfactorily turning for home, gave no response when asked for efforts final 300 M.

Bumped at start, niggled along to race 1 to 2Ls off the lead, checked losing ground at 600 M, travelled only fairly 3-wide rounding bend, could not find extra to challenge the principal in the home straight. (Lame left front leg.)
Slow to begin, taken back 4 to 5Ls behind the leaders, pulled in early stages, could not handle the turn, made no impression in the home straight.
Out in line, taken rearward 5Ls off the speed, carried 4-wide and drifted back to last turning for home, well beaten. (Mucus.)

Taken across behind runners, raced as the back marker 7Ls off the lead, improved round the outside of field nearing 400 M and quickened impressively in straight to reel in the long time leader final 25 M.
Towards the rear and not hurried in early and middle stages, swung wide into straight, had plenty to do but made good headway from 300 M to go 2nd just before the line.
Went forward from draw 12 and crossed to the lead, set even tempo and travelled strongly to straight, was produced with every chance but got tired late on and couldn't hold off challenges on outside.
Broke well from draw 1, with leaders early then sat back in midfield passing 1200 M and was difficult to settle, came through horses to challenge inside 250 M, kept on well to the line.
Held inside running in mid-division, 5Ls behind leader as they turned for home, made steady progress down the inside final 200 M.
In touch, raced 3-wide throughout and left with no cover from 1200 M, stayed on in straight without looking dangerous to the first three.
Held up behind midfield, bustled along over the home turn and had 5Ls to make up coming off the bend, ran into traffic 150 M then stayed on in closing stages.
Positively ridden and tracked leader 2-wide in 3rd, made a mild rally in the run to the line, never looked likely and was outpaced inside 100 M.
Placed in mid-division 2-wide and well covered, waited with till 350 M, found less than expected in the finish and could only stick on at the one pace final 200 M.
Patiently ridden towards the rear 6-7Ls back, angled out from the fence approaching 400 M, soon ran into traffic and didn't have a clear crack throughout the straight.
Went forward and obtained the fence before the 1st turn, sat behind the lead one back but was outpaced making the turn for home, found no response in the finish and weakened rapidly over 200 M out.
3-wide in midfield throughout, found nothing in the finish and was left behind nearing 200 M. (Jockey questioned re riding position.)
